es    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Search for images   The Library provides access to image resources and databases of digitized photographs, postcards, posters and letters from sources beyond our collections.      Image Search Resources  Chicago or Illinois history   Explore Chicago Collections  Illinois Digital Archives   For all subject areas   Digital Public Library of America  Europeana  UIC image collections  Explore Chicago Collections   Images of Works of Art  ArtStor  A specialized database of art images, with over 2 million items.  Research Guide to Art History  Links to more databases of art imagery that the Library subscribes to, as well as freely available databases that specialize in art.  Images for Health Sciences and Medical Research  Subject and research Guides for Health Sciences topics contain links and advice for finding images. Some databases of medical textbooks provide separate search access to the textbook illustrations and photos. Some examples:   Health Sciences Gateway: Images, Audio and Video  Biomedical Visualization: Images, Audio and Video   Open Access Images  If you’re looking for images that you’re free to re-use, try the following resources:  Flickr Search   Look for photos with a Creative Commons license—use the “any license” drop-down to make a choice.  Some photos require you to give attribution to the photographer, or you can only use the photo for a non-commercial purpose  Important: photographers can change their license terms at any time!   Wikipedia Public Domain Image Resources   Art images, stock photo images and more that can be freely used.         Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sci